INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','One should die proudly when it is no longer possible to live proudly.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The "kingdom of Heaven" is a condition of the heart - not something that comes "upon the earth" or "after death."');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','He who fights with monsters might take care lest he thereby become a monster. Is not life a hundred times too short for us to bore ourselves?');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Is life not a thousand times too short for us to bore ourselves?');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Regarding life, the wisest men of all ages have judged alike: it is worthless.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','We love life, not because we are used to living but because we are used to loving.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','A casual stroll through the lunatic asylum shows that faith does not prove anything.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','A friend should be a master at guessing and keeping still: you must not want to see everything.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','A great value of antiquity lies in the fact that its writings are the only ones that modern men still read with exactness.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','A pair of powerful spectacles has sometimes sufficed to cure a person in love.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','A woman may very well form a friendship with a man, but for this to endure, it must be assisted by a little physical antipathy.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','After coming into contact with a religious man I always feel I must wash my hands.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Ah, women. They make the highs higher and the lows more frequent.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','All sciences are now under the obligation to prepare the ground for the future task of the philosopher, which is to solve the problem of value, to determine the true hierarchy of values.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','All things are subject to interpretation whichever interpretation prevails at a given time is a function of power and not truth.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','All truth is simple... is that not doubly a lie?');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Although the most acute judges of the witches and even the witches themselves, were convinced of the guilt of witchery, the guilt nevertheless was non-existent. It is thus with all guilt.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','And we should consider every day lost on which we have not danced at least once. And we should call every truth false which was not accompanied by at least one laugh.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Anyone who has declared someone else to be an idiot, a bad apple, is annoyed when it turns out in the end that he isn''t.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Art is not merely an imitation of the reality of nature, but in truth a metaphysical supplement to the reality of nature, placed alongside thereof for its conquest.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','At times one remains faithful to a cause only because its opponents do not cease to be insipid.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Before the effect one believes in different causes than one does after the effect.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Behind all their personal vanity, women themselves always have an impersonal contempt for woman.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Blessed are the forgetful: for they get the better even of their blunders.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Character is determined more by the lack of certain experiences than by those one has had.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Do whatever you will, but first be such as are able to will.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Does wisdom perhaps appear on the earth as a raven which is inspired by the smell of carrion?');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Every church is a stone on the grave of a god-man: it does not want him to rise up again under any circumstances.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Every man is a creative cause of what happens, a primum mobile with an original movement.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Experience, as a desire for experience, does not come off. We must not study ourselves while having an experience.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Extreme positions are not succeeded by moderate ones, but by contrary extreme positions.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Faith: not wanting to know what is true.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Fanatics are picturesque, mankind would rather see gestures than listen to reasons.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','For the woman, the man is a means: the end is always the child.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Glance into the world just as though time were gone: and everything crooked will become straight to you.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Go up close to your friend, but do not go over to him! We should also respect the enemy in our friend.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','God is a thought who makes crooked all that is straight.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Great indebtedness does not make men grateful, but vengeful; and if a little charity is not forgotten, it turns into a gnawing worm.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','He that humbleth himself wishes to be exalted.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','He who cannot give anything away cannot feel anything either.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','He who has a why to live can bear almost any how.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','He who laughs best today, will also laughs last.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','He who would learn to fly one day must first learn to stand and walk and run and climb and dance; one cannot fly into flying.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','I assess the power of a will by how much resistance, pain, torture it endures and knows how to turn to its advantage.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','I cannot believe in a God who wants to be praised all the time.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','I love those who do not know how to live for today.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','I still live, I still think: I still have to live, for I still have to think.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','If a woman possesses manly virtues one should run away from her; and if she does not possess them she runs away from herself.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','If there is something to pardon in everything, there is also something to condemn.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','If you gaze long into an abyss, the abyss will gaze back into you.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','In every real man a child is hidden that wants to play.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','In heaven, all the interesting people are missing.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','In individuals, insanity is rare; but in groups, parties, nations and epochs, it is the rule.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','In large states public education will always be mediocre, for the same reason that in large kitchens the cooking is usually bad.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','In praise there is more obtrusiveness than in blame.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','In the consciousness of the truth he has perceived, man now sees everywhere only the awfulness or the absurdity of existence and loathing seizes him.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It is always consoling to think of suicide: in that way one gets through many a bad night.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It is good to express a thing twice right at the outset and so to give it a right foot and also a left one. Truth can surely stand on one leg, but with two it will be able to walk and get around.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It is impossible to suffer without making someone pay for it; every complaint already contains revenge.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It is my ambition to say in ten sentences what others say in a whole book.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It is not a lack of love, but a lack of friendship that makes unhappy marriages.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It is not when truth is dirty, but when it is shallow, that the lover of knowledge is reluctant to step into its waters.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','It says nothing against the ripeness of a spirit that it has a few worms.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Love is blind; friendship closes its eYes.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Love matches, so called, have illusion for their father and need for their mother.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Many a man fails as an original thinker simply because his memory it too good.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Many are stubborn in pursuit of the path they have chosen, few in pursuit of the goal.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','No one lies so boldly as the man who is indignant.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Not when truth is dirty, but when it is shallow, does the enlightened man dislike to wade into its waters.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Nothing has been purchased more dearly than the little bit of reason and sense of freedom which now constitutes our pride.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Of all that is written, I love only what a person has written with his own blood.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','On the mountains of truth you can never climb in vain: either you will reach a point higher up today, or you will be training your powers so that you will be able to climb higher tomorrow.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','One may sometimes tell a lie, but the grimace that accompanies it tells the truth.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','One must still have chaos in oneself to be able to give birth to a dancing star.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','One ought to hold on to one''s heart; for if one lets it go, one soon loses control of the head too.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Our treasure lies in the beehive of our knowledge. We are perpetually on the way thither, being by nature winged insects and honey gatherers of the mind.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Our vanity is hardest to wound precisely when our pride has just been wounded.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','People who have given us their complete confidence believe that they have a right to ours. The inference is false, a gift confers no rights.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Perhaps I know best why it is man alone who laughs; he alone suffers so deeply that he had to invent laughter.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Rejoicing in our joy, not suffering over our suffering, makes someone a friend.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Shared joys make a friend, not shared sufferings.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Sleeping is no mean art: for its sake one must stay awake all day.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Some are made modest by great praise, others insolent.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Stupid as a man, say the women: cowardly as a woman, say the men. Stupidity in a woman is unwomanly.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Success has always been a great liar.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The best author will be the one who is ashamed to become a writer.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The best weapon against an enemy is another enemy.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The Christian resolution to find the world ugly and bad has made the world ugly and bad.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The demand to be loved is the greatest of all arrogant presumptions.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The desire to annoy no one, to harm no one, can equally well be the sign of a just as of an anxious disposition.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The doer alone learneth.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The essence of all beautiful art, all great art, is gratitude.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The future influences the present just as much as the past.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The man of knowledge must be able not only to love his enemies but also to hate his friends.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The most common lie is that which one lies to himself; lying to others is relatively an exception.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The press, the machine, the railway, the telegraph are premises whose thousand-year conclusion no one has yet dared to draw.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The surest way to corrupt a youth is to instruct him to hold in higher esteem those who think alike than those who think differently.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The true man wants two things: danger and play. For that reason he wants woman, as the most dangerous plaything.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','The world itself is the will to power - and nothing else! And you yourself are the will to power - and nothing else!');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There are no eternal facts, as there are no absolute truths.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There are no facts, only interpretations.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There are various eYes. Even the Sphinx has eYes: and as a result there are various truths, and as a result there is no truth.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There is a rollicking kindness that looks like malice.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There is always some madness in love. But there is also always some reason in madness.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There is an innocence in admiration; it is found in those to whom it has never yet occurred that they, too, might be admired some day.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There is in general good reason to suppose that in several respects the gods could all benefit from instruction by us human beings. We humans are - more humane.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There is not enough love and goodness in the world to permit giving any of it away to imaginary beings.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','There is nothing we like to communicate to others as much as the seal of secrecy together with what lies under it.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','These people abstain, it is true: but the bitch Sensuality glares enviously out of all they do.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','This is the hardest of all: to close the open hand out of love, and keep modest as a giver.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','This is what is hardest: to close the open hand because one loves.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Those who cannot understand how to put their thoughts on ice should not enter into the heat of debate.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Thoughts are the shadows of our feelings - always darker, emptier and simpler.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','To be ashamed of one''s immorality: that is a step on the staircase at whose end one is also ashamed of one''s morality.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','To forget one''s purpose is the commonest form of stupidity.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','To live is to suffer, to survive is to find some meaning in the suffering.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','To use the same words is not a sufficient guarantee of understanding; one must use the same words for the same genus of inward experience; ultimately one must have one''s experiences in common.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Today I love myself as I love my god: who could charge me with a sin today? I know only sins against my god; but who knows my god?');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','War has always been the grand sagacity of every spirit which has grown too inward and too profound; its curative power lies even in the wounds one receives.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','We do not hate as long as we still attach a lesser value, but only when we attach an equal or a greater value.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','We hear only those questions for which we are in a position to find answers.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','We often refuse to accept an idea merely because the tone of voice in which it has been expressed is unsympathetic to us.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','We should consider every day lost on which we have not danced at least once. And we should call every truth false which was not accompanied by at least one laugh.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What can everyone do? Praise and blame. This is human virtue, this is human madness.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What do you regard as most humane? To spare someone shame.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What does not destroy me, makes me stronger.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What doesn''t kill us makes us stronger.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What is good? All that heightens the feeling of power, the will to power, power itself in man.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What then in the last resort are the truths of mankind? They are the irrefutable errors of mankind.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','What? You seek something? You wish to multiply yourself tenfold, a hundredfold? You seek followers? Seek zeros!');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whatever is done for love always occurs beyond good and evil.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','When a hundred men stand together, each of them loses his mind and gets another one.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','When marrying, ask yourself this question: Do you believe that you will be able to converse well with this person into your old age? Everything else in marriage is transitory.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','When one does away with oneself one does the most estimable thing possible: one thereby almost deserves to live.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','When one has finished building one''s house, one suddenly realizes that in the process one has learned something that one really needed to know in the worst way - before one began.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','When one has not had a good father, one must create one.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','When you look into an abyss, the abyss also looks into you.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever battles with monsters had better see that it does not turn him into a monster. And if you gaze long into an abyss, the abyss will gaze back into you.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever despises himself nonetheless respects himself as one who despises.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever does not have a good father should procure one.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever feels predestined to see and not to believe will find all believers too noisy and pushy: he guards against them.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever fights monsters should see to it that in the process he does not become a monster. And if you gaze long enough into an abyss, the abyss will gaze back into you.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever has provoked men to rage against him has always gained a party in his favor, too.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Whoever has witnessed another''s ideal becomes his inexorable judge and as it were his evil conscience.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','Women are considered deep - why? Because one can never discover any bottom to them. Women are not even shallow.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','You have your way. I have my way. As for the right way, the correct way, and the only way, it does not exist.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Friedrich Nietzsche','You say it is the good cause that hallows even war? I say unto you: it is the good war that hallows any cause.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Fritz Perls','I am not in this world to live up to other people''s expectations, nor do I feel that the world must live up to mine.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','If I were again beginning my studies, I would follow the advice of Plato and start with mathematics.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','I''ve loved the stars too fondly to be fearful of the night.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','All truths are easy to understand once they are discovered; the point is to discover them.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','I do not feel obliged to believe that the same God who has endowed us with sense, reason, and intellect has intended us to forgo their use.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','I have never met a man so ignorant that I couldn''t learn something from him.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','I think that in the discussion of natural problems we ought to begin not with the Scriptures, but with experiments, and demonstrations.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','It is surely harmful to souls to make it a heresy to believe what is proved.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','It vexes me when they would constrain science by the authority of the Scriptures, and yet do not consider themselves bound to answer reason and experiment.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','Measure what is measurable, and make measurable what is not so.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','Nature is relentless and unchangeable, and it is indifferent as to whether its hidden reasons and actions are understandable to man or not.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','The Bible shows the way to go to heaven, not the way the heavens go.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','We cannot teach people anything; we can only help them discover it within themselves.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('Galileo','Where the senses fail us, reason must step in.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','And like the old soldier in that ballad, I now close my military career and just fade away, an old soldier who tried to do his duty as God gave him the sight to see that duty.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','I''ve looked that old scoundrel death in the eye many times but this time I think he has me on the ropes.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Only those are fit to live who are not afraid to die.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','The soldier above all others prays for peace, for it is the soldier who must suffer and bear the deepest wounds and scars of war.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Our country is now geared to an arms economy bred in an artificially induced psychosis of war hysteria and an incessant propaganda of fear.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Our government has kept us in a perpetual state of fear - kept us in a continuous stampede of patriotic fervor - with the cry of grave national emergency.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Life is a lively process of becoming.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','A better world shall emerge based on faith and understanding.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Age wrinkles the body. Quitting wrinkles the soul.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Always there has been some terrible evil at home or some monstrous foreign power that was going to gobble us up if we did not blindly rally behind it.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Could I have but a line a century hence crediting a contribution to the advance of peace, I would yield every honor which has been accorded by war.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Duty, Honor, Country. Those three hallowed words reverently dictate what you ought to be, what you can be, what you will be.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','I am concerned for the security of our great Nation; not so much because of any threat from without, but because of the insidious forces working from within.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','I have known war as few men now living know it. It''s very destructiveness on both friend and foe has rendered it useless as a means of settling international disputes.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','In my dreams I hear again the crash of guns, the rattle of musketry, the strange, mournful mutter of the battlefield.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','In war there is no substitute for victory.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','It is fatal to enter any war without the will to win it.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','Never give an order that can''t be obeyed.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','The best luck of all is the luck you make for yourself.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','The world is in a constant conspiracy against the brave. It''s the age-old struggle: the roar of the crowd on the one side, and the voice of your conscience on the other.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','There is no security on this earth; there is only opportunity.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','There is no substitute for victory.');
INSERT INTO `QUOTES` (AUTHOR,QUOTE) VALUES ('General Douglas MacArthur','We are not retreating - we are advancing in another direction.');
